			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Account Executive<br />
(Salt Lake City, Utah)</strong></p>
<p>
<strong>Company Overview</strong><br />
It&#39;s not every day that a hot, Silicon Valley software company chooses Salt Lake City to open an office and hire great sales people. So what does Gild (www.gild.com) do? - The world is changing fast as a stream of new companies drive innovation.&nbsp; Behind the next big idea or the next billion dollar company are always good, technically-proficient people there to make it happen.&nbsp; However, those people are becoming increasingly harder to discover and assess.&nbsp; As has been displayed on every syndicate lately, this shortage of technical talent has reached consequential levels.</p>
<p>
Gild solves this by truly illuminating who&rsquo;s talented via a science-based SaaS (Software as a Service). We find the people that aren&#39;t&nbsp; being found and we illuminate their true technical talent for a golden opportunity. Gild is growing fast with over 100 customers added in just 9 months.&nbsp; We are backed by Steve Anderson of Baseline Ventures, SAP Ventures, Globespan Capital Partners, investor Mark Kvamme and are headquartered in beautiful San Francisco where new employees will visit!</p>
<p>
Where you can help?<br />
We&rsquo;re based in San Francisco but we&rsquo;re hiring Software Sales for an Inside Role in Salt Lake City, Utah.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Sell one of the hottest, most functional SaaS (Software as a Service)&nbsp; platforms on the market today.</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Target and Develop new prospects by using Data.com, Linked-in, Twitter and the phone.&nbsp;</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Be aggressive and build your book of business by scoping and hunting down new clients-that&#39;s the fun part of the job</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Find the key decision makers and close the sale</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Manage all renewals and upsell existing accounts</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Plan and implement call/email marketing campaigns to attract new prospects</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Continuously learn and maintain in-depth knowledge of company&rsquo;s products and services, industry trends and competition</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Be a team player who knows how to contribute team revenue</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Demonstrate excellent sales prospecting, negotiating and closing skills-know how to sell</span></li>
</ul>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
<strong>Desired Expertise:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Minimum of two years of successful prospecting, negotiating and closin into large enterprises, service providers, and partners</li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree</span></li>
<li>
Worked with a top CRM--preference of SalesForce.com</li>
<li>
Excellent verbal and personality skills</li>
<li>
Able to work in fast-paced, self-directed entrepreneurial environment</li>
<li>
Exceptional written communication skills</li>
<li>
Strong organization and presentation skills</li>
<li>
Excellent time management skills</li>
<li>
Highly energetic and self-starter</li>
<li>
Able to multi-task the activities with shifting priorities</li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Experience working in a Cloud-based (SaaS) technology is a plus.</span></li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
Again, it&#39;s not every day that a hot, Silicon Valley software company chooses Salt Lake City to open an office. Our sales compensation plan (including stock) is designed to support our aggressive growth objectives. We have an excellent management team with some of the brightest people in the industry and you will be coached to greatness.&nbsp; Our environment is team driven, fast paced, customer focused and competitive in the market.&nbsp; Gild has aggressive marketing plans in place to support the sales team&rsquo;s effectiveness and we also offer full training, growth potential, autonomy and a chance to join a fun, hard-working team in a Silicon-Valley start up environment.</p>
