			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Data Scientist (www.gild.com)</strong></p>
<p>
<strong>Company:</strong></p>
<p>
HR and recruiting have been begging for innovation. That&rsquo;s why Gild is here. Gild exists to bring meritocracy to the professional world by providing hiring solutions that illuminate who&rsquo;s talented. Companies use Gild&rsquo;s patent-pending hiring solutions to find and engage the best candidates out there. Unlike professional networks and job boards, Gild&rsquo;s solutions tell companies how good different prospects are, and provide the social insights hiring teams need to engage prospects effectively. &nbsp;Launched in 2011, Gild is backed by Steve Anderson of Baseline Ventures, SAP Ventures, Globespan Capital Partners, investor Mark Kvamme and is headquartered in San Francisco, CA.</p>
<p>
<strong>Objective:</strong></p>
<p>
You will have a huge impact on the design and development of new features for www.gild.com as well as the enhancement of existing features and applications.&nbsp; Gild is building a next generation social and mobile search engine that will change the world of recruiting forever.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Work on a small data science team in charge of data mining, predictive modeling and analytics design.<br />
&bull; Work closely with a product engineering team to identify and answer important product questions<br />
&bull; Answer product questions by using appropriate statistical techniques on available data<br />
&bull; Communicate findings to product managers and engineers<br />
&bull; Drive the collection of new data and the refinement of existing data sources<br />
&bull; Analyze and interpret the results of product experiments<br />
&bull; Develop best practices for instrumentation and experimentation and communicate those to product engineering teams</p>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; B.S. or M.S. in a relevant technical field, or 4+ years experience in a relevant role<br />
&bull; Extensive experience solving analytical problems using quantitative approaches<br />
&bull; Comfort manipulating and analyzing complex, high-volume, high-dimensionality data from varying sources<br />
&bull; A strong passion for empirical research and for answering hard questions with data<br />
&bull; A flexible analytic approach that allows for results at varying levels of precision<br />
&bull; Ability to communicate complex quantitative analysis in a clear, precise, and actionable manner<br />
&bull; Fluency with at least one scripting language such as Python<br />
&bull; Expert knowledge of an analysis tool such as Python (Numpy/SciKits/PyMC), R, or Matlab<br />
&bull; Experience working with large data sets, experience working with distributed computing tools a plus (Map/Reduce, Hadoop, Hive, etc.)<br />
&bull; Preferred: Bayesian statistical methods, including Monte Carlo simulations (MCMC, Gibbs sampling and Metropolis-Hastings), optimization techniques, mixed models, Bayesian networks and hierarchical models</p>
<p>
<strong>Compensation:</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Competitive Base Salary<br />
&bull; Attractive Stock Option Plan<br />
&bull; Health/Dental/Vision/401k<br />
&bull; Opportunity to work with committed, talented people with a great sense of humor</p>
]]></description>
