			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Product Marketing Manager</strong></p>
<p>
<strong style="font-size: 12px;">Company Overview</strong></p>
<p>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Gild (www.gild.com) -- Tech recruiting has been begging for innovation. That&rsquo;s why Gild is here. Gild provides hiring solutions that harness the power of data to liberate hiring teams from the challenges of finding developers. Using patent-pending technology, Gild evaluates the work of millions of developers so companies using Gild&rsquo;s talent acquisition tools know who&rsquo;s good and can target the right candidates.&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12px;">Launched in 2011, Gild is backed by Steve Anderson of Baseline Ventures, SAP Ventures, Globespan Capital Partners, investor Mark Kvamme and is headquartered in San Francisco, CA</span><span style="font-size: 12px;">.</span></p>
<br />
<p>
<strong>Candidate Profile</strong></p>
<p>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Gild is looking for a Product Marketing Manager that can act as a key strategic partner in product strategy and customer communications. You&rsquo;ll be charged with creating marketing communication materials that enhance the user experience and increase customer usage and understanding of our products.&nbsp; You&rsquo;ll also help maintain the product feedback loop so that customer feedback is seamlessly integrated into product development, and will be in charge of scoping out new product opportunities as Gild continues to grow. You must be a powerful strategic thinker with strong technical and analytical skills, and should be able to work cross-functionally with Product and Customer Success to maximize the success of Gild&rsquo;s products.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p>
We&#39;re a fast-paced, hardworking group that prizes openness, proactivity, and critical thinking.&nbsp; You&rsquo;ll be an integral part of Gild&rsquo;s marketing team, representing the voice of the customer.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Generate compelling and easy to understand marketing content that will illuminate product benefits to customers and enhance the customer experience<br />
&bull; Maintain our ongoing product feedback loop by collecting and analyzing customer feedback, reviewing usage analytics and using the data to inform product strategy<br />
&bull; Conduct positioning and messaging exercises to clarify product vision and communications<br />
&bull; Partner with Product team to keep up-to-date on product enhancements<br />
&bull; Communicate benefits of new product enhancements to customers to ensure they perceive the full benefits of product improvements<br />
&bull; Ensure that Customer Success team is aware of product changes and has the information needed to communicate with customers<br />
&bull; Measure and report on the effectiveness of initiatives and communication materials<br />
&bull; Explore new product opportunities by conducting relevant market research, including segmentation, market sizing, and competitive research<br />
&bull; Evaluate and optimize pricing models for new and current products in accordance with revenue goals</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Bachelor&rsquo;s degree required; MBA is a plus<br />
&bull; 3 - 5 years of related product marketing experience with a proven track record of successfully managing marketing programs that meet business objectives and target metrics<br />
&bull; Strong writing skills with experience generating marketing communication materials<br />
&bull; Understanding of and experience with technical products<br />
&bull; Experience collecting and analyzing both quantitative and qualitative feedback<br />
&bull; Detail-oriented with strong organizational and project management skills<br />
&bull; Strong strategic thinking, creative problem solving, technical and analytical skills<br />
&bull; Ability to flourish in a fast-paced, high-growth environment<br />
&bull; Demonstrated ability to drive cross-functional teams to meet business objectives and influence co-workers while fostering strong working relationships<br />
&bull; Excellent verbal, written, visual/presentation skills<br />
&bull; Not required, but an added plus, experience in the recruiting space</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Compensation</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Salary commensurate with experience<br />
&bull; Health/Life/Dental/Vision/401k<br />
&bull; Opportunity to work with committed, talented people with a great sense of humor<br />
&bull; Stock options</p>
]]></description>
